# Conventional Commits

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) for every commit message.

## Format

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <subject>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **subject**: imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period, max 72 characters
- **scope**: optional area of change (e.g. `giveaway`, `overlay`, `auth`, `collector`, `deps`)
- **body**: explain *why*, not *what*, when the change is non-obvious

## Types

| Type | Use for |
| --- | --- |
| `feat` | New user-facing behavior |
| `fix` | Bug fixes |
| `docs` | README, DEPLOY, comments only |
| `style` | Formatting, whitespace (no logic change) |
| `refactor` | Code change that is neither feat nor fix |
| `perf` | Performance improvements |
| `test` | Tests only |
| `build` | Build system, Docker, dependencies |
| `ci` | CI/CD configuration |
| `chore` | Maintenance that does not fit above |

Breaking changes: add `!` after type/scope (`feat(api)!: …`) or a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.

## Examples

```
feat(giveaway): add confirmation countdown after draw
fix(overlay): sync confetti timing with wheel completion
docs: document Coolify deploy steps
build(deps): sync bun.lock after auth upgrade
chore: setup commitlint and husky hooks
```

## Validation

Commit messages are checked by commitlint via the Husky `commit-msg` hook. Invalid messages are rejected before the commit is created.
